# Coding Standards

## TypeScript Guidelines
- Always use TypeScript for new files
- Define proper interfaces and types
- Use strict type checking
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for consistency

## React 19 Patterns
- Use function components with hooks
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use React 19 features like `use` hook when appropriate
- Follow Next.js 15 App Router patterns

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Prefer ShadCN UI components over custom ones
- Use CSS modules only when necessary
- Follow responsive design principles

## File Naming
- Use kebab-case for files: `user-profile.tsx`
- Use PascalCase for components: `UserProfile`
- Use camelCase for functions and variables